pros:
--Good money (commissions);
--Great coworkers;
--Highly reduced price on cable and internet for your own home;
--Pretty decent product which is competitive on the market.

cons:
--Low base salary;
--Internal red tape added weeks to the sales process...it was easier to sell a deal to a customer than it was to sell to internal decision makers;
--Management controls their employees through fear...if you have one bad month they hang a "sales improvement plan" (aka Write-up) over your head...from that point on the clock is ticking and you better produce or you're gone. Yes, this is sales and you must produce...but managing through fear is not a good way to motivate your people.
